Welcome!

I am Francesco Giordano, I am PhD student at HEC Paris, within the doctoral program of the Institute Polytechnique de Paris. 
I am generally interested in topics of game, decision theory, and mechanism design specifically to aspects of learning and information. 
I am also genuinely interested in topics related to entrepreneurship and innovation, specifically to the decision making process behind the selection, value creation (e.g. through mentorship) and evaluation of startups. 
# I am interested in topics related to multiagent systems, finance (private equity, hedge funds, market structures), data science 

Other:
I am collaborating to the ION Management Science Lab
I am alumnus of QTEM and since my graduation I have been often coach for the QTEM Data Challenge 
